{
  "stem": "1858.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I lived in that camp for two years, not knowing how the war was progressing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "For, as I said, we were totally, totally cut off from the rest of the world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Out of the 2,000 girls that worked in our factory, there was only one escape.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Had the girl that managed to escape-- I don't know if she survived the escape.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Had she known what will happen to us, what punishment we would have to endure, I don't think she would have made an attempt.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In our factory, there were Czech citizens working in the factory, for Ober Altstadt was a part of Germany that actually belonged to Czechoslovakia at one time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were a lot of Czech people living in that section of Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And, obviously, some who worked in the factory were also in the Czech underground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And, somehow, they managed to smuggle her out of the factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But what happened, our [NON-ENGLISH], the head of our concentration camp, was a woman, who, before the war, was just factory worker, whose power was the growth of the camp, became more vicious, whose name also happened to be Irma Hoffmann.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the girl who managed to escape was also named Hoffmann.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we don't know if it was that she feared that somebody might accuse her of having something to do, or because she was angry that one of us could manage to escape, I cannot tell you of the punishment we had to endure.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "No food, and, of course, cell appel without an end.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We just stood there until we were collapsing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I think that had the girl known what will happen because of her escape, I don't think she would have escaped.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We didn't find out after the war whether she was alive or not.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
